<h2>4 · Explain Your Lesson Code 🎥</h2>
<p>In today's live lesson you cleaned the inputs in your own game. Now explain that code in a short video on your phone (or a parent's phone). You may show your game running. Teach it like the viewer has never coded. Try to use these words: <strong>clean</strong>, <strong>strip</strong>, <strong>lower</strong>, <strong>in</strong>, <strong>spelling</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show one <code>ask()</code> line from your game and read your <code>.strip().lower()</code> out loud.</li>
<li>Explain what <code>.strip()</code> and <code>.lower()</code> each do to the player's answer.</li>
<li>Read your <code>if ... in [ ... ]</code> line and say which spellings you allowed.</li>
<li>Run it once with a "normal" answer and once with a different spelling, and show both reaching the same path.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
